By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The National Leader of the All Progressives Congress, Asiwaju Ahmed Tinubu has condolenced with His Eminence, Sultan of Sokoto, Alhaji Sa’ad Abubakar, over the passing of his elder brother, Alhaji Buhari  Abubakar III. Tinubu who took to his twitter handle to express his deepest condolences, described Alhaji Abubakar III as an excellent community leader who impacted the people of his Sokoto North District positively. According to him, late Alhaji Abubakar III  was also a devoted Muslim who contributed immensely towards the propagation of Islam in his domain and beyond. “May Almighty Allah console and comfort him and the entire Abubakar family over this loss, Tinubu said. The former Lagos governor prayed Almighty Allah to give the wife, children and indeed all those he left behind the strength to live with his demise. “May He guide, guard and protect them through this difficult moment, Tinubu added. SOKOTO - The Sultan of Sokoto, Alhaji Sa'ad Abubakar III, on Monday said traditional rulers and politicians were partners in progress and not enemies or competitors. Abubakar said this when the new Emir of Kano, Alhaji Muhammadu Sanusi II, paid him a courtesy call in Sokoto.. ``Politicians and traditional rulers… In "News" By Ibukun Emiola Ibadan - Alhaji Muhammad Sa’ad Abubakar III, the sultan of Sokoto, has enjoined muslims to be peaceful and refused to be provoked to take up arms to fight over any issue or comment made by anybody in the country.  The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Abubakar… In "News" Ado-Ekiti  -  The Sultan of Sokoto, Alhaji Muhammadu Abubakar III, has admonished Muslim leaders to educate the youth against engaging in terrorism. Alhaji Abubakar spoke during the installation of the new President-General, League of Imams and Alfas in Southwest, Sheikh Jamiu Kewulere, in Ado-Ekiti on Saturday. ``Occasions like this are… In "News"